<br>
Also, will see about getting us on the rotations for Fear/Hate again now that our membership has built back up.<br>
<br>
There are many wonderful places to raid and there are many of us working on our epics.  However...I do Not want to schedule too many raids.  I think we had too many going on with CoM every week and other things last summer.  It took the fun out of the game and the guild for me.  I was feeling obligated to go on these raids until I reached the point where I just didn't want to do them any more.<br>
<br>
So, in order to keep our raids a special fun time for us to gather together and kick butt, I really don't want to plan more than 1 high, 1 mid-low, and 1 event each month.  At least for now.  As the guild expands and grows, we may increase that.  (who knows, one day we may be doing 3 raids a week like KTF and the other uber guilds)<br>
<br>
I still want to hear where you want to go and raid.  Popularity will certainly be a factor in when we do certain raids.  If everyone seems to want to go to one location, we will do that raid before one where only a few want to go.<br>
<br>
Also - Keep an eye on our Allies boards.  They raid too and are usually pretty willing to have us there to kick butt with them.  And don't restrict yourselves.  Just becuase you're in BC doesn't mean you can't go raid with other guilds and groups of your friends.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
*If you need to guild yourself with another guild to raid with them so you can hear instructions in guildchat, let an officer know before you do, and they'll be sure to get you re-invited to BC after the raid is over.<br>
<br>
/ramble off   <br>
<br>
Let's go have some fun.  And don't be too discouraged if we don't raid your favorite dungeon right away.<br>
